<div id="t1"><h3>Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood (Japanese: 鋼の錬金術師 Hepburn: Hagane no Renkinjutsushi?) is an anime series adapted from the Fullmetal Alchemist manga by Hiromu Arakawa. Produced by Bones, the series is directed by Yasuhiro Irie and written by Hiroshi Ōnogi. Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood is the second anime television series based on Fullmetal Alchemist, the first being 2003's Fullmetal Alchemist, as a 1:1 adaptation directly following the events of the manga. It was first announced in the manga series' 20th tankōbon volume.</h3></div>
</br>
